          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single parchment folio. Shelfmark: F2020.1.3. Qur'ānic text: Q 18:56-58. Lines per page: 16. Dimensions: 305 x 600. Script style <hi rend="italic">kūfī </hi>type F.I. At the moment only the image of the fol 1 r is given by the institution.  </p>
              <p>Cf. also the website of the institution: <ref target="https://www.si.edu/object/folio-quran:fsg_F2020.1.3">https://www.si.edu/object/folio-quran:fsg_F2020.1.3</ref>. </p>
            </summary>
            <msItem xml:id="mysql_id_698566" n="1r">
              <title type="numeric" key="018:056:001-018:058:018">
                                    018:056:001-018:058:018
                                </title>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc>
              <supportDesc>
                <support>
                  <p>Text division: Simple verse separator consists of three oblique strokes placed one above the other diagonally. Illuminated <hi rend="italic">ʾalif </hi>in green, red and brown ink is placed to mark every fifth verse. </p>
                </support>
                <extent>Folios: 
                                    <dimensions unit="mm"><width>305</width><height>600</height></dimensions>
                                </extent>
              </supportDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc>
              <handNote/>
            </handDesc>
            <scriptDesc>
              <summary>
                <p>Diacritics: Two layers of marking the letters can be traced in the manuscript. The two kind of diacritical marks differ in the shape and ink that was used. Vocalisation is made by red and green dots. Line-fillers in the shape of small streaks are placed at the end of a line to fill out the space to the margin.  </p>
              </summary>
